    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-11-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-12-21T19:55:00Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Emergency Senior Citizens Relief Act of 2010 - Amends the Assistance for Unemployed Workers and Struggling Families Act, title II of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Tax Act of 2009, to extend: (1) through 2011 the $250 economic recovery payments to recipients of Social Security, Supplemental Security Income (SSI) (title XVI of the Social Security Act), railroad retirement benefits, and veterans disability compensation or pension benefits; and (2) through 2011 the special tax credit for certain government retirees.</p> <p>Makes additional appropriations through FY2013 to cover such payments.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
